9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 912, L.D. 1390, “Resolve, Directing the
10 Secretary of State to Develop a Plan for a Multiyear Registration System for National Car
11 Rental Companies”
12 Amend the resolve by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, Directing the Secretary of State to Develop Recommendations for a
14 Multiyear Registration System for National Car Rental Companies'
15 Amend the resolve by striking out everything after the preamble and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. Recommendations for multiyear registration system. Resolved: That
18 the Department of the Secretary of State, Bureau of Motor Vehicles, with input from the
19 Department of Public Safety, Bureau of State Police, shall consider and develop
20 recommendations on how to implement a multiyear registration and inspection program
21 for national car rental companies in the State.
22 Sec. 2. Submission of report. Resolved: That the Secretary of State shall submit
23 a report detailing how a multiyear registration and inspection program for national car
24 rental companies may be implemented in the State pursuant to section 1 along with
25 legislation necessary to accomplish the objectives outlined in the report to the Joint
26 Standing Committee on Transportation by December 3, 2025. The Joint Standing
27 Committee on Transportation may report out legislation based on the report to the Second
28 Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.'
29 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
30 section number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment replaces the resolve. The amendment requires the Department of the
3333 Secretary of State, Bureau of Motor Vehicles, with input from the Department of Public
3344 Safety, Bureau of State Police, to consider and develop recommendations on how to
